Add Toyota Motor analysis via company-analyzer (Healy×Damodaran)
Run the uploaded company-analyzer framework (W1–W8 + orchestrator) on
Toyota Motor (7203), producing interview-prep material for the FY2026
(year ended March 2026) results.

Primary sources: FY2026 決算要旨 (2026/5/8), H1 FY2026 半期報告書, and the
統合報告書2025 (referenced by URL). Peer financials, WACC and ratings
gathered from company IR / SEC filings.

Key findings:
- No.1 element: profit/balance-sheet resilience — ¥3.77T operating profit
  (7.4% margin) despite a ¥1.38T US-tariff hit, in a year peers (Ford,
  Honda, Nissan, Stellantis) posted net losses.
- Value gap (W7, centerpiece): automotive operating ROIC ~16.5% >> WACC
  ~7%, yet consolidated ROE ~10% (vs 20% aspiration) because ~¥33T of
  low-return capital (cash, cross-holdings, equity-method) dilutes it.
  ROE bridge: ~¥15T capital return over 3–4 yrs -> ROE ~15–19%.
- INTERVIEW_PACK integrates the resume (Shiga Univ / Miyanishi seminar,
  KINTO/Toru Route, Vibe coding, Thailand study tour) into why-Toyota,
  Q&A, reverse questions, and weakness rebuttals.

